The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, February 20, 2004 				 Cash custodian cop jailed
																								Burdwan, Feb. 19: The district court today sentenced sub-inspector Golam Murtaza to 10 years in prison for stealing Rs 2.5 lakh from its storeroom, of which he was in charge, reports our correspondent. 																								On April 1, last year, the money meant to be policemens salaries was stolen from the courts malkhana (storeroom). Murtaza was arrested but obtained bail. The police took him into custody immediately after additional special judge B.K.Moitra passed the order today.																								Then court inspector Amal Talukdar had lodged a complaint against Murtaza after the theft. 																								The additional public prosecutor of the court said Murtaza had withdrawn Rs 5 lakh from the treasury office on March 31 last year to pay salaries to sub-inspectors. Salaries were disbursed among some of them the same day and the rest of the money was kept in the storeroom cash box. 																								When the cash box was opened on April 1, there was no money in it. The box was neither broken nor was there any sign of the use of force to get the money out, the prosecutor said.
